          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Campaign Transparency Act</b></p> <p>This bill amends the Federal Election Campaign Act of 1971 to:</p> <ul> <li>eliminate the dollar amount thresholds for mandatory reporting of the identity of persons making contributions (generally in the aggregate amount or value in excess of $200 within the calendar year or election cycle) to political committees in federal elections; and</li> <li>so require reporting the identification of all persons making contributions within the calendar year or election cycle to such committees, regardless of the amount.</li> </ul>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2015-12-17T05:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
